{ The standard response - White has tried in practice also   7.Ng5  and   @@StartFEN@@rnbqr1k1/pppp1ppp/5n2/8/1bP1p3/2N2NP1/PP1PPPBP/R1BQ1RK1 w - - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7.Ne1  after which Black takes on c3 immediately and the queenside knight not necessarily will go to c6. }
7... Nc6 8. Nc2
{ The best move because   8.Nxc6  is not a serious alternative, Black continuing with  8...dxc6  instantly winning the battle for the center. Black will continue with ...Bf5 and ...Qd7, pressuring the white d-pawn. After White’s d3 or d4 Black wants to take on d3, making it a weakness. }
