Bd2
{ With the white bishop on d2 the black queen retreats to d6. If White jumps with the knight on d2 immediately, the queen retreats to d8. If White includes a3, Black responds with ...a5 and the same ideas with minor differences. }
10... Qd6 11. Bc3 { White is threatening with Nxe5 and d4 next. } 11... Rd8 12.
Nd2 Be6
{ Black wants to play ...Bd5 next. White can't play   13.Nc4  due to the  ...Bxf2+  threat, followed by ...Bxc4 and ... Qc5+, if necessary. This trick might work in several lines, if White is not careful. }
13. Qa4
{ 13.Ne4  is tempting but after  ...Qe7  14.Nxc5  Qxc5  White doesn't have a serious follow-up as after  15.Rc1  Black can just grab the pawn on a2 with  ...Bxa2 }
13... Nd4 14. Rfe1 Bd5 15. Ne4 Qe7 { Black has everything under control. } *

