[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1. Rare Lines"]
[Black "Chapter 1 Exercise: #1"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "2kr3r/ppp1qpp1/2p5/2b2b1p/2P1pPn1/1P2P1P1/PBQPB2P/RN2K2R w KQ - 0 12"]
[SetUp "1"]

12. h3
{ White is trying to push back Black's attacking pieces from the kingside and castle long. Is there a way to punish White for the chosen strategy? }
12... h4
{ Black sacrifices a piece to open the h-file and since the black knight is on  g4  , White can't do anything about it!  12...Nxe3!  As a matter of fact, this move should win as well!  13.dxe3  Bxe3  Black has a very dangerous attack. }
13. hxg4 hxg3 14. Rg1
{ White is not interested to win a second piece, as the back rank weakness should quickly decide the game in favor of Black.  14.Rxh8  Rxh8  15.gxf5  Rh1+  16.Bf1  g2  Black is about to promote to a queen. }
14... Rh1
{ This is one of the greatest moves in the history of chess! Black sacrifices a whole rook, just to win a single tempo for the ...g2 threat! }
15. Rxh1 { White has nothing better. } 15... g2
{ Because of the unfortunate placement of the white queen on c2, the white king can never escape to the queenside. }
16. Rf1 Qh4+ 17. Kd1 gxf1=Q+
{ And a mate in a few moves. 0-1 Larsen,B @@StartBracket@@2650@@EndBracket@@-Spassky,B @@StartBracket@@2670@@EndBracket@@ Match/Team URS-World }
