{ This is much riskier as Black quickly gets a strong initiative. } 11... e4
12. Nd2 Qg5 13. g3 Bg4
{ Black has already developed all of his pieces while the white king is still in the center. }
14. Qc2 Qh5 15. h3 Be2
{ White has the extra pawn but at a great cost - the king is stuck in the center. }
