15... Kh8 16. Nfd2
{ After  16.d4  Nxd4  and not missing the Neg5 threat Black is doing just alright. The immediate  @@StartFEN@@4rr1k/1ppbq1pp/1nnb4/p3p3/4N3/PP1P1N2/1BQ1BPPP/R3R1K1 w - - 1 16@@EndFEN@@  16.Bf1  not only allows Black to play 16...Bg4 but there's also an interesting exchange sacrifice.  16...Rxf3!?  17.gxf3  Nd5  with big compensation. For example,  18.d4  Nf4  19.dxe5  Bxe5  20.Ng3  Qf6  and the knight on f4 might be worth a rook. }
