10. Nc4 c6
{ Black doesn't give White any break - it's all about the speed of the attack. }
11. bxc6
{ After  11.b6  Black can castle short and already take back the pawn on b6 with a big advantage. }
11... b5 12. Ncd2
{ Falling back on b2 looks very awkward but it's possible - Black would continue the attack with  12...Ra6  Retreating with the knight to d2 allows Black to execute a very beautiful idea. }
