Nxd4 Nxd4 10. Qxd4 O-O 11. Nc3
{ Jones,G @@StartBracket@@2670@@EndBracket@@ -Kalashian,D @@StartBracket@@2398@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com Titled Tuesday 2020. Here instead of the queen trade, Black should have developed his pieces. }
11... Be6
{ Castling long for White is a little dangerous due to the exposed king. } 12.
O-O-O Qc8
{ Black should be able to start the attack at the queenside much faster than White has even thought about anything at the kingside. The white king is pretty exposed. In the next few moves Black wants to continue with moves like ...Bb3, ...Rd8 and ...Bf6, avoiding the queen trade. }
