6... Bxc3 7. Bxc3 Nf6
{ Black is solid and doesn't need the ...h6 move anymore which is typical for the mainline as White's dark-squared bishop is not creating any problems there. The only thing White might think of is trying to keep the black king in the center but it just doesn't work. }
8. cxd5 { White has to include it otherwise ...dxc4 already is a threat. } 8...
cxd5 9. e3
{ 9.Bb4  to keep the Black in the center fails - Black just continues with  9...Nc6  and ...Qa5+ next. If necessary, Black can always play ...Ne7 to close the diagonal and castle afterward. }
