6. a3
{ Black is quite happy to take on c3 anyway, and here White generously gifts a tempo to do this. }
6... Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Nf6
{ White doesn't have enough pressure against Black's center to claim a good game. }
8. cxd5 cxd5 9. Bg5
{ This is one of those rare occasions when the dark-squared bishop will get to g5 before Black can play ... h6 but it won't stay there for long. }
9... Nbd7 { Black already is better due to White's weak light squares. } *

