13. Qd3
{ The most logical move - White is aiming for c4 while also keeping an eye for the knight on e4 and the safety of the king. }
13... Nc6 14. Bf5
{ This would be an interesting idea how White could challenge the blockade - if necessary, Black can retreat for a couple of moves, regroup and then go back. }
14... Nd6 { The safest move. } 15. Ba3 Ne7
{ Black closes the potential pin and prepares to play ...Nc4 next to get rid of the dark-squared bishop. }
16. Bh3 Nc4 17. Bb4 a5 { Forcing the trade on e7. } 18. Bxe7 Qxe7
{ Now all Black needs to do is to defend the d5 pawn properly. } 19. Rf5 Rad8
20. Bg2 Qe6 21. Rb1 g6
{ The last accurate move before playing ... Nd6 is to remove one of the attackers. }
