[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3. Early g3: 3.d4 without Qb3"]
[Black "Chapter 3 Exercise: #3"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rn1qr1k1/pp3pp1/7p/3p4/3Pn3/B1P3PB/P3P2P/R2Q1RK1 w - - 0 14"]
[SetUp "1"]

14. Qb3
{ This is one of the critical positions of Chapter 3 - Black has two knights vs two bishops and it's of paramount importance to block the center, otherwise, the bishop pair could become deadly. White is attacking the b7 and d5 pawns - what will you do? }
14... Na6
{ With the moves 13.Ba3 Re8 included, now Black can't play  14...Nc6  as after  15.Qxb7  the f7 pawn will be under attack as well. }
15. Qxb7 Nc7
{ Black is threatening with ...Rb8 and the pawn on a7 can't be taken because of ...Ra8 and the white bishop falls. }
16. Qc6 { This immediate retreat makes most sense. } 16... Ne6
{ Black has an excellent compensation for the pawn and has successfully blocked the center. }
