9. Qd1 b4
{ Black pushes the white knight to the edge of the board where it contributes little to the position and also is not challenging Black's center. }
10. Na4 Nf6 11. Nh3 Bd6 12. Bg2 Nbd7
{ Black is more than fine here and his light pieces control the most critical squares around the center. }
