17. Qxd4 Nxd4 18. Bb2 { White is pinning the two knights. } 18... Nxe2+ 19. Kf2
Nxf4 20. Bxf6 Nxg2 { White will recapture the piece but is still down a pawn. }
21. Rg1 Bh3 { An important accuracy, winning a tempo. } 22. Kg3 Be6 23. Rxg2
Kh7
{ The arising position probably is drawn but it's White who needs to find it. Black wants to keep at least one pair of rooks to hope to win, otherwise, in the opposite color bishop endgame there's not much to do. }
