[SetUp "1"]

19. Qb2
{ This position is from an important theoretical line - White has just pinned the black queen and intends to take the d-pawn. What did White miss? }
19... Nd3
{ The knight can't be taken because the white rook on d1 is under attack! } 20.
Qd2
{ White appears to be alright - now the knight is under attack again. What should Black do here? }
20... dxc4 { Black sacrifices a piece for a stunning idea. } 21. exd3 c3
{ White has to give up the rook on d1 in order not to experience the wrath of two passed pawns on the 3rd rank. }
