5. Qb3
{ White is immediately pressuring the black pawn on d5 - what important idea should you know here? }
5... dxc4
{ If White has not included cxd5 and plays Qb3 right away, very often you will have access to this maneuver, followed by ...Be6.   Needless to say,  5...Nf6  would allow White to increase pressure with  6.cxd5  cxd5  7.Bg5  ,  and White got everything he wanted. }
6. Qxc4 Be6 7. Qa4 f5
{ Black has an easy development and at some point later can even win some extra tempos with ...Nb6-d5. }
