{ Black has a deadly attack. No matter where you look, White is busted. } 14.
Qc5 { Or  14.Qc3 } 14... Rc8
{ Here White faces a terrible choice, none of them good. } 15. Qe5+ Be6
{ It's important to keep the knight on d4 with the threats of Nc2+ and Rc1+. }
16. Na3 { 16.Qxd4  would meet the same idea of  ...Rc1+  winning the bishop. }
16... Nc6 17. Qf4 Nd5 18. Qxe4
{ Just when it might seem that Black is happy to take the bishop on d6, he can go for more! }
18... Qa5+ 19. Kd1 Nde7 20. Bxe7 Kxe7
{ The unfortunate placement of the king and the multiple threats decide the game in Black's favor. }
