Rc1 Nc5 16. b4
{ This line is double-edged and by no means an easy decision for White. } 16...
Nd3 17. Nxd3 exd3 18. e4
{ This move cuts off support from the pawn on d3 but seriously weakens the kingside. Now comes the eternal question - is the pawn on d3 a weakness or a strong passed pawn? }
18... Qe5
{ The pawn on e4 is taboo because of a pin at the e-file. Black improves the queen to position it either on f4 or d4 and is considering to push ...h5. }
19. Qf3
{ White is racing to win the pawn on d3 thus Black has to conjure something quickly. }
19... h5 20. gxh5
{ This allows White to win the pawn but with a terrible position.  20.Qxd3  hxg4  is just equal. }
20... Nxh5 21. Nc4 Qg5 22. Nxd6 Nf4
{ This position illustrates how quickly things can go wrong for White - it doesn't feel that Black is missing a pawn here. }
