8... cxd5
{ Again, an important accuracy - you'll see the difference if Black will forget to include this move! }
9. cxd5 d6 10. O-O { White finishes the development but so does Black. } 10...
Bf5 { Black is strengthening the center and setting up a little trap. } 11. f3
{ 11.Nxe4  would be a huge blunder here because of  11...Bxe4  12.Bxb4  Bxg2  and the incoming ... Qe4+ which would cost White a full piece. }
