{ Of course, Black doesn't want to blunder Qh5+. This is a start of a forced sequence, where Black wants to reroute his bishop to f6 and win material. If White is prematurely retreating with the knight, queen trade and total domination at the queenside should decide the game in Black's favor. }
20. b3 Rc2 { Black needs to take care of White's dark-squared bishop first. }
