24. Rxe2 Bxg5 25. Qh3 f4
{ White inevitably parts ways with his pride - the light-squared bishop. } 26.
g4 f3 27. Bxf3 exf3 28. Qxf3
{ Even though White has a rook and 3 pawns for two bishops, those are truly monstrous bishops! }
28... Rf8
{ Black should be able to convert this position to a win. For example,  29.Qxb7  Bxg4  and White should lose more material soon. }
