18... Qf7
{ All of this is a forced sequence. It might seem that Black is eyeing for the pawn on a2 but actually, the big prize lies at the kingside where a very strong attack is about to begin. Castling is not even necessary as Black is ready to attack. }
19. b3 { This allows Black to start a decisive attack at the kingside. } 19...
Qh5 20. f3 f4
{ Black has enough pieces to storm the white king while White's pieces are tied down to the first rank. }
21. g4 Qg5 22. Bb2 Bc5
{ This can't end well for White, with the entire army undeveloped and the king - exposed. }
23. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 24. Kh1 h5
{ Black is looking for ways to open the position and mate the white king. } 25.
Nc2 hxg4 { The loss of the bishop on d4 is not important anymore. } 26. Nxd4
Qh4
