15. b3
{ This plan makes for me the most sense as it includes in the game also the queen. }
15... Re8
{ This is the only game so far in the line, played in a correspondence game in 2019. This continuation to me feels a little artificial as now Black's kingside is vulnerable - I would have opted for this continuation if the f-pawn was still on f7. In the game, Black managed to score an impressive positional win, which involved a second pawn sacrifice by simplifying the position in the process. }
16. Bb2 Qe7
{ Black went for a bishop trade on a3 which is only possible if White allows it and plays Nd2 as well. It might not be easy to repeat this in an actual game over the board and understand all of the nuances. }
17. Nd2 Ba3 18. Bc3 Bb4 { Black insists on the trade. } 19. Bxb4 Qxb4
{ With the dark-squared bishops traded, Black's task is easier and he went on to win the game in 52 moves. You will be able to study the game in the Model Games chapter. Beltins,G @@StartBracket@@2138@@EndBracket@@ - Doronkin, S @@StartBracket@@2186@@EndBracket@@ EU-ch 2019 pr06 email 2019. }
