16... Rae8
{ Black has finished his development, his control of the center is firm, and there are no weaknesses. After a couple of trades, the position will inevitably open and the power of the extra exchange will start to make a difference. }
17. d4 e4
{ It is possible, that also  17...exd4  works here, but I'm somewhat concerned about White's piece activity and the exposed black king. The text move at least closes one of the white bishops. }
18. Rc1 Qd8 19. Ne5
{ 19.Nd2  b5!  again stops the white knight from landing on c4. } 19... Be6
{ There's no need to rush with the trade - the knight is not going anywhere. Now that the pawn structure has been fixed, it makes sense to fight for the c-file. }
