{ The only move which keeps the protections of the e5 pawn.   17...Bc6  is not an alternative here and would be premature as the freshly created pin is quite annoying. For example  18.d4  e4  19.d5! }
18. d4
{ This is one of the ideas that Black needs to be aware of at any given moment and closing the position, most notably the light-squared bishop on g2 seems to be the safest continuation. }
18... e4 19. Ne5 Re7
{ 19...Be6  runs into  20.d5!  with an idea of Nd7 fork. Black just needs to watch out for some tactical tricks and penetrate White's ranks through the c-file. A typical ...b5 at some point might be a good idea to take away from White the c4 square as he might think about pushing e3, followed by Bf1-c4. }
