{ The simplest choice, to relieve the pressure in the center with an upcoming ...dxc4,  keeping the e4 pawn.  6...e3!?  is an interesting way to complicate matters by ruining White's pawn structure but White doesn't have to accept the sacrifice and instead plays  7.Nxc5  Qa5+  8.Nc3  exf2+  9.Kxf2  with a complex game. }
7. Bd2
{ White is happy to trade the bishops - Black shouldn't mind as well. Playing  7.N1d2  would leave Black with a wide set of pleasant choices, among the simplest  7...exd3  ,  followed by a normal development and White's position seems weird. }
7... Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2
{ Again, taking with either of the knights on d2 makes almost no sense and Black could just continue with ...exd3 and a great game. }
