{ White simply doesn't have the time to include this move as Black's reaction is swift. }
5... dxc4
{ Since the knight on d4 is hanging, White has no time to recapture the pawn on e4. }
6. Nc2
{ The only thing White can do here is to play an improvised gambit as it's impossible to win back the pawn. }
6... f5 7. Ne3
{ This is an alternate plan but neither this one brings White any joy. } 7...
Be6 8. a4
{ White prepares to play Na3 to recapture the pawn on c4 but this is too slow. The immediate  8.Qc2  would meet  8...Qd4  and the black queen feels quite comfortable there. }
8... Nd7 9. Na3 Ne5 10. Qc2 Qd4 { White is already busted. } 11. g4 f4 12. Nf5
Bxf5 13. gxf5 f3
{ Chennaoui,Y @@StartBracket@@2087@@EndBracket@@ -Motylev,A @@StartBracket@@2640@@EndBracket@@ Lisbon Portugal rapid 2op 2020, Black won a crushing game. }
