8... Bxd4
{ I find this to be the simplest move order -  8...Nf6  is also good but it allows White to play  9.Nb3  will feel a concession with the typical f3 setups in this chapter. }
9. exd4 Qxd4 10. fxe4
{ Or  10.Qe2  Nf6  should lead the same but Black can also try to improve things by playing  10...Ne7  ,  still going for the ...c5 and ...Nc6 setup, but also directly leading the kingside knight to e5 via g6. }
