{ Black's plan here is simple - prepare ...c5 and ...Nc6, getting a good grip of the e5 and d4 squares. They're outposts! The immediate  10...Ne7  is inaccurate because of  11.Qa4!  and Black is not ready to fight for the center. This is why ...Nf6 applies the pressure against the e4 pawn. }
11. Qe2 c5 12. Nb5
{ The most ambitious choice - White goes for a direct development won't cause Black any trouble. }
12... Qd8 13. Qd3
{ This is a very inspired play! White is trying to make good use of the knight on b5, threatening with Nd6+ and if possible - Nc7 to win some material. }
13... Nc6
{ Very often the best approach to meet unorthodox plans is with simple and classic moves - Black is continuing the development. }
14. Qxd8+ { 14.Nd6+  would lead nowhere as Black will just play  14...Ke7 }
14... Kxd8 15. d3 Be6 16. Bf4
{ White's last chance is to go after the c5 pawn and try to open the position and thus make good use of his two bishop advantage. }
16... a6
{ It's better to push away the annoying knight as quickly as possible. } 17.
Nc3
{ 17.Nc7  would lead to trade on e6 where Black's knights are not worse than the white bishops, perhaps on the contrary, due to the outposts in the center. But after  17.Nd6  b6  ,  Black is not even obliged to trade the bishop for the knight and has a very solid position. }
17... Ke7 18. Rc1 Rac8 19. Na4
{ White seemingly has made a progress and the pawn on c5 is about to be lost, but Black has a fantastic resource. }
19... Nb4 20. a3
{ The most challenging - everything else is not demanding Black to be very precise. }
20... Na2
{ What a paradoxical solution - Black voluntarily imprisons his knight on a2 but with a clear purpose to play ...b5 next. }
21. Ra1 { Not mandatory but the most tempting. } 21... b5
{ Instead of the standard Nc3 which would force the exchange of the knights and an equal position, White could march forward with Nb6 and at the right time Nc4, cutting off access from the knight on a2 but also sacrificing his own in the process. In any of the scenarios Black will have a great compensation for the sacrificed pawn and can focus on something else while White is busy capturing the knight. Black's queenside pawns can arrive to help the knight with ...b4 quite quickly. }
