10. f3
{ This idea is a common motif - White forces the pawn trade, is opening the f-file, and planning to gran a pawn center with the following d4 and e4. The only problem with that plan is that Black has no weaknesses and it can pressure the center pretty quickly. }
10... exf3 11. Bxf3
{ Lagarde,M @@StartBracket@@2599@@EndBracket@@-Prithu,G @@StartBracket@@2470@@EndBracket@@ Purtichju op 6th 2019. }
11... Bh3 { This looks more logical than what was played in the game. } 12. d4
Qe6 13. Re1 O-O 14. e4 Rad8
{ All of these moves seem to be necessary although White could postpone moving forward the e-pawn for a bit. Black is going to position both rooks on the d-file and e-file and pressure those central pawns with his pieces. At the right time, the ...c5 thrust could give Black a good grip over the e5 square, making it a nice outpost. }
