{ The final nuance - since Black is threatening with ...Bg3+, ... Qh2+ and ...Rf6+ next, White has to do something about it. }
32. Bb4+ Bd6+ 33. Kg1 Bxb4 34. axb4 { Now Black finally crashes through. }
34... Qh2+ 35. Kf1 Rf6+ 36. Ke1 Qg3+ 37. Kd1 Rf2
{ Black wins the queen or delivers a checkmate with the simple ...Qxg2, should the white queen try to escape. }
