12... g5
{ The way White has played out this opening, there's nothing better as the black pawn on e4 is about to be lost. Including ...Nb4 first might be an alternative but I have a feeling that they will lead to the same positions. }
13. hxg5 Qxg5 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4
{ Also here White has won a pawn but Black's initiative can become deadly very quickly. }
15... h4 16. g4 Nc5 17. Qf3
{ White wants to rearrange his pieces so the h-pawn must go as well. } 17... h3
18. Bxh3 Qg6 { The white king is in the crossfire. } *

