12. exd3
{ What is the most precise move here for Black and most importantly - what does White want to do? }
12... Qd4
{ A paradoxical decision but it's important to stop the white d-pawn advancement.   12...O-O  This natural move illustrates the potential problem.  13.d4  Qc7  14.d5  White opens the position and Black's piece placement together with the h-pawn feels awkward. }
13. Nc2 Qg4
{ Another important accuracy but probably the more natural   13...Qd8  was playable as well. }
14. Bf4 Qxd1 15. Raxd1 Bg4
{ Black has successfully finished the development and should block the d-pawn's advancement. Castling long is a good way to start, bringing the light-squared bishop to e6. }
