{ White plans to fight for a strong pawn center with d3-e4, move the knight and push f4. This is something that Black wants to avoid, otherwise, there might be a risk to wind up in a position with no counterplay as the center will be difficult to open, especially taking into account those two white bishops. Under normal circumstances White probably doesn't want to push d4 as the pawn on c4 will become an eternal weakness and an easy target for Black. }
