8... Nbd7 { This was the other move I was considering. } 9. e4 Nc5 10. f3
{ White is about to push d4 and win a couple of tempos - Black has no time to prepare and execute ...d5 as the knight on d7 is in the wrong place to do that. Black is sort of solid but lacks an active plan, and the white knight from e3 is going to control pretty much the entire center, and also guarding the c4 pawn. }
