8... h6
{ This is my proposed novelty but first, let me explain how I got there. Checking other possible continuations here I concluded that every single of them comes with some sort of a concession. The text move is a great addition in almost every scenario to stop the future  Bg5  from happening and being ready to play ...e4,  should the situation demand it. I wasn't comfortable with shoving ...e4 here immediately because the white knight is still standing on e1.  So after  8...e4  White could continue with  9.f3  ,  force the pawn trade and go back with the knight to f3, continuing with d3 and e4. Probably it's not much but the text move I like a little better there.   Finally, if White is about to push  8.e4  himself, this will give Black enough time to organize a counterplay at the queenside with c6 and either  8...d5   or  8...b5  . }
