11. Ne3
{ White has done everything to prevent Black from pushing the pawn forward. }
11... d5
{ Black does it nevertheless! The speed and timing are important as one move late and it might find in a passive position with no active prospects. }
12. exd5 cxd5
{ This trade seems to be quite forced as it opens White's bishop on g2 and now White has some options here. }
13. d4 { Either this or  13.f4  ,  White could try to strike at the center. }
13... exd4 14. cxd4
{ Necessary as  14.Qxd4  would meet  14...Nc6  and White is dropping a pawn on c4. }
14... Nc6 15. Rb1 Re7
{ A great maneuver as the rook on the 7th rank will protect both b7 and d5 pawns and is ready to pressure the white pawn on d4. }
16. Ba3 Rd7 { Black controls the d5 square. } *

