{ This trade seems to be quite forced as it opens White's bishop on g2 and now White has some options here. }
13. f4
{ Quite an extravagant move, promising a lot of interesting lines - White is opening the f-file and fighting for the center. }
13... exf4
{ I think this is much simpler than  13...d4!?  which leads to some crazy lines and long-term compensation after  14.Bxb7  . }
14. gxf4 d4
{ The problem with the immediate  14...dxc4  is that after  15.Bxb7  Nbd7  with the same exchange sacrifice idea is impossible due to  16.f5  and Black drops a piece. }
15. cxd4 Bxc4
{ One lovely shot after another - White has a ruined pawn structure. If White won't accept the bishop, Black can just retreat with it to a6 and protect the pawn on b7. The pawn on b7 will force both sides to trade rooks and the white squared bishops, leaving the white king very much exposed. }
16. Nxc4 Qxd4+ 17. Kh1 Qxa1
{ This is the end of a forced sequence. Now White would have to pick up the best move. }
18. Qb3
{ White is now threatening to win the black queen with Bb2. It's interesting that the tempting  18.Nd6  meets a cold response  18...Qb1!!  Black gives up an exchange and a pawn but takes over the game pretty quickly. }
18... Qd4
{ Black has an extra exchange and a pawn but White is about to win it all back. }
19. Bb2
{ Or  19.Ne5  Nbd7  20.Bb2  Qb6  21.Qxf7+  Kh8  and it is interesting dynamic equality on the board. }
19... Qd8 20. Bxb7 Nbd7
{ Now it's all about the initiative - White shouldn't accept the exchange and focus on the attack instead. Black remains very solid and can at any given time give up the exchange. }
21. Nd6 Qe7 22. Nf5 Qe6 23. Qh3
{ White is storming forward with everything he's got. } 23... Rab8 24. Nxh6+
{ Or  24.Rg1  g6  . } 24... Kh7
{ The white knight can't be taken because of  24...gxh6  25.Qxh6  and Rg1+ incoming. }
25. Nf5+ { 25.f5  Qe2! } 25... Kg8 26. Rg1 g6
{ White has got nothing better than a perpetual check. Don't be scared of this entire line - it's just an illustration of how the game might proceed and there are a million ways how it might get diverted moves before. }
