{ A powerful counterpunch - Black is threatening to play ...Na5 next so White has to take one of the pawns. }
14. Nxd5
{ This is the second most reasonable move since  14.Bxd5  doesn't look like an alternative because of  14...Na5  15.Qb5  a6  and Black immediately regains the material on d5. }
14... e4
{ Black effectively cuts off White's light-squared bishop, and its colleague at the queenside is not feeling better. The material balance doesn't matter anymore and it's all about the control of the squares which White is rapidly losing. }
15. Qxb7
{ White can try to take the greedy approach but this loses even more time. }
15... Nxd5 16. Qxc6 Rc8
{ An important intermezzo move - Black has activated all of his pieces while the same can't be said about White. }
17. Qb7 Nb6
{ Black has a great initiative. If the black knight will make it to f3, it already feels game over for White as the light squares will decide the fate of the game. }
*

