8... c6 { This was one of the main candidate moves I was considering here. } 9.
d3 h6 10. Nc2
{ I wasn't sure I like the position as ...c6 is linked with an idea to play ...d5 later. White is also threatening to play e4 and if now Black would push ...e4, this would leave the pawn on d6 as a weakness, since c6 has already been included. }
10... d5
{ The entire approach of pushing the d-pawn before White has played e4 seems to be a risky strategic approach. }
11. Ne3 Be6 { Now after  12.Qb3  White is pushing. } *

