8. d3 { White wants to play e4 next - what should you do about it? } 8... e4
{ With the black rook already on e8, it makes sense to thwart White's idea. }
9. Nd4 h6
{ Black should keep the pawn on e4 as long as he can, thus limiting White's light-squared bishop's range. }
10. Rb1 Nbd7 11. Qc2 Nc5
{ Black can increase the defense of the e4 pawn by bringing more pieces. White could take on e4 himself but this would seriously weaken his queenside pawn structure. }
