9... b6 10. g4 Nd7 11. O-O Ba6
{ Here White has an interesting choice to continue the initiative with either the quiet waiting move  12.Rf2  or what Svidler played in the game;  12.Ng3 }
12. Rf2 Na5 13. Ng3
{ The idea is to remove the rook from the pin so that the light-squared bishop can be preserved. }
13... Bxc4 14. Bc2 d5
{ Here we have an interesting position. White can certainly look forward to launching an inspired attack at the kingside since both bishops on c2 and c1 are contributing and then there's the entire kingside arsenal. Since Black has no weaknesses, his chances to hold should be pretty good. }
