9. Be3 Be6 10. Be2 Nc6
{ Black has a simple plan - play ...Na5 and open the position a little. The loss of a couple of tempos in a closed position is not very important - it's called maneuvering. }
11. O-O Na5 12. b3
{ The alternative  12.c5  doesn't look good at all since Black can just respond with  12...d5 }
12... axb3 13. axb3
{ With the position already opened, Black can even retreat with the knight on c6 and reroute the other to c5 via d7. However, here is a nice tactical shot that Black should be aware of. }
13... b5 14. cxb5 Nxb3
{ The position opens up a little more to give the black knights more targets. }
15. Rab1 Ra3 { Black looks very active here. } *

