8. Nh3 Nc5 9. Nf2 Nc6
{ Since White has 'wasted' a tempo on b3 and long castling doesn't look so simple anymore, Black is thinking about the ...f5 push but there's no need to hurry with it, including castling short. Black can include two more easy moves and then figure out where exactly this game is heading. In the meantime, White also is watching Black - an ambitious player might castle the opposite but if White castles long, so can Black. }
10. Qc2
{ 10.Be3  would just transpose to a similar line we just covered. With the text move, White might want to reroute his knight from f2 to d5. }
10... O-O
{ The most principled approach to go with ...f5. In the meantime, Black has to be aware that White might attempt to block his idea and run towards the queenside. }
11. g4
{ The inclusion of  11.Be3  b6  shouldn't change anything and the game could proceed to the same setup. }
11... Qh4 12. Be3 Nd8
{ The black knights are the perfect blockade - the white pawns aren't moving forward. For example,  13.O-O-O  Nde6  14.Nd3  b6  . }
