[White "11. Two Knights: 4.e4 and 6.f3"]
[Black "Chapter 11 Exercise: #1"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbq1rk1/pp1p1ppp/2p2n2/4p3/2P1P3/2PP2P1/P4P1P/R1BQKBNR w KQ - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

7. g4
{ Since Black wants to break the center with ... d5, what will you do if White will try to stop you with the g4-g5 threat? }
7... d5
{ The correct answer is - play it anyway! If necessary, sacrifice a pawn. } 8.
g5 Nfd7 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. exd5 Qa5
{ Even if Black doesn't win back the pawn immediately, his lead in development is significant. }
