[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "11. Two Knights: 4.e4 and 6.f3"]
[Black "Chapter 11 Exercise: #2"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rn1qk2r/1pp2ppp/3pbn2/4p3/p1P1P3/2P2PP1/PP3N1P/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 0 9"]
[SetUp "1"]

9. f4
{ One of the ideas of White positioning the knight on f2 in this position is to prepare the pawn march at the kingside. What will you do? }
9... exf4
{ Open the position and avoid a scenario where White is slowly squeezing Black due to a considerable space advantage. The white pawn on e4 makes a fine target. }
10. gxf4 Qe7
{ White's central pawns are now static and not moving forward. Black can complete his development. }
11. Bd3 Nc6 12. Qe2 O-O-O
{ As long as Black won't open the a-file for the white rook, he has nothing to worry about. }
