8... a6 9. Rd1
{ This move was played between two Chinese players and here the standard  9...b5  made a lot of sense to initiate the traditional initiative at the queenside. I assume Black was concerned with  10.c5  however after  10...Bb7!  Black has the upper hand and can sacrifice the pawn on d6 if necessary. The white pawn on e4 is about to fall. }
