{ Black is ready to push the b-pawn and open the queenside. Here White should have played  12.b3 }
12. a3
{ This weakens a lot of white squares at the queenside. The experienced Chinese GM masterfully exploited them. }
12... Nb3 13. Ng5 Bd7 14. Bf1 a5
{ Black fixes the weaknesses at the queenside. } 15. g4 a4 16. Qf2 b6
{ Du,S @@StartBracket@@2399@@EndBracket@@ -Zhang,Z @@StartBracket@@2640@@EndBracket@@ Chinese Team championships 2006, Black went on to win an impressive positional game. White lacks an active plan and the weaknesses at the queenside are catastrophic. }
