11. Nf1
{ This early knight's rerouting is interesting but it gives Black just enough time to make a breakthrough in the center. }
11... Re8
{ Black is waiting for White to play f3 first as Ne3 would leave the pawn on e4 under attack. Here you have two potential ideas - either go after the d-pawn push or ...c6-b5, depending on availability. }
12. f3 c6 13. Ne3
{ If White would include  13.Ba3  ,  then Black can switch over to  13...Qb8  and push the b-pawn forward and the bishop on a3 will definitely feel misplaced and almost obliged to trade on c5. }
13... d5 { After mass trades on d5 Black has a comfortable position. } *

