Bxe4 16. Rxe4 Nd7
{ More accurate than trading the rooks first and then developing the knight as White could continue with the annoying Rd1 with some practical problems. Here the white queen is not on e4 yet and Black can play ...Qf6 with a tempo. Black is interested to trade off as many heavy pieces as he can and then there's the ...f6 resource to both protect the king and let it out of the cage. Black is still keeping his extra pawn. }
17. Qxc3 Qf6 18. Rxe8+ Rxe8 19. Re1
{ Since there's no more attack and all that's left is some tactical tricks, Black looks fine. White already is desperately looking for ways to win back the pawn. }
