9. Nxe5 dxe5
{ This is by far the simplest choice in Black's arsenal. Now come a few forced moves. }
10. Bxe4 Nd7 11. d4 Nf6
{ White is enjoying his two bishops and a center but Black has no weaknesses and can target the center quickly. }
12. Bg2
{ Matlakov,M @@StartBracket@@2694@@EndBracket@@ -Neiksans,A @@StartBracket@@2631@@EndBracket@@ European Blitz Championships 2016. }
12... exd4 { Black needs some targets, thus the pawn trade is the best. } 13.
cxd4 Bg4
{ Black wants to play ...Qd7 and trade-off the light-squared bishops. The other rook belongs on d8, and Black should including ...h6 at some point to make sure that White has no access to Bg5. }
14. Qd3 Re8 15. Be3 Qd7 16. Rfe1 h6
{ This doesn't look like a big improvement for White as the dark-squared bishop on e3 is quite passive. Ideally Black could trade off the light-squared bishops on play ...b5 to take over the d5 square for the knight. }
