[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnbq1rk1/ppp2ppp/3p1n2/4p3/2P1P3/2P3P1/PP3PBP/R1BQK1NR w KQ - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

7. Ne2
{ One of the most important moments of the arising pawn structure will be for Black to understand - what's the best plan here? Since White is going for a positional squeeze, it's important to plan an active plan early on. }
7... a6
{ Every single plan has the same backbone - it starts with a pawn push. The white knight on e2 appears to be misplaced, should the position open at the queenside. }
8. a4 { White would like to keep things closed but it's already too late. }
8... Be6 9. b3 Nbd7 10. Qc2 Nc5 11. a5
{ One final attempt to close the queenside and focus on a long squeeze. Black is a little faster. }
11... b6 12. axb6 cxb6 13. O-O a5
{ Black has successfully opened the queenside and has clear targets. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
