[SetUp "1"]

11. f4
{ White would like to trade the pawns and then claim the center with d4, backed by two bishops. What's the most active way to meet it? }
11... e4
{ This is a positional pawn sacrifice! Black is about to establish dominance over the light-squares. }
12. Bxe4 Re8 13. d3 Bh3 14. Rf2 Nf6
{ There's a fair chance that White will give back the extra pawn himself to get some activity, otherwise Black will control all of the light-squares that will be occupied by the knights, while White's dark-squared bishop is a useless piece. }
