{ With the white queen on c3 you should recognize the idea to open the position as quickly as possible. The alternative  7.dxc3  would allow Black to improvise a little. Instead of the traditional ...d6 Black could opt for the more powerful  7...e4  ,  fixing those light-squared weaknesses at f3 and d3. }
7... d5 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Qb3
{ Kveinys,A @@StartBracket@@2530@@EndBracket@@-Jasnikowski,Z @@StartBracket@@2440@@EndBracket@@ Polish Team championships 1996. Here Black should have gone for a known pawn sacrifice to accelerate the attack. }
