5. Qc2
{ White is not defining his setup just yet but mainly it comes with two ideas. First, threaten a3 so that White can recapture on c3 with the queen, and second, keep an eye on the e4 square so that Black meets extra pressure if he'd go for the e-pawn push in a near future. }
5... Re8
{ The biggest downside of White's plan is that Black can immediately fight for a strong pawn center and the inclusion of Qc2 doesn't help White to combat it. Normally Black doesn't mind trading the bishop on c3 but I'd suggest refraining from doing it immediately - White might 'talk' you into it by adding another move a3. }
6. Nf3
{ This position bears a direct resemblance to the mainline of the entire line, covered in the next chapter. Instead of the traditional short castle, White has played Qc2 which is not stopping Black from taking the center. }
6... c6 { Black intends to play ...d5 next. } 7. O-O d5 8. cxd5 cxd5 9. d4
{ This line has some minor popularity as the white knight inevitably gets to e5. }
9... e4 10. Ne5 Nc6
{ White will have to take on  c6  - the tricky  11.Rd1  would just postpone the decision by one move as Black could include the useful  11...h6   If you don't like the arising position, there's a quiet alternative  10...h6  with an idea to play ...Be6 and ...Nbd7 next. }
11. Nxc6 bxc6
{ Black already looks better here - he enjoys the space advantage and can organize an offensive at the kingside. The only weakness is on c6 which can be defended with ...Rc8. White might position his knight on c5 via a4 but it's not doing there anything real. }
12. Na4 Bd7
{ Black protects the pawn on c6 and 'invites' the white knight to c5. Black should be focusing on the kingside. }
13. Nc5 Bg4
{ Threatening to take on c5 and White can't recapture with the queen as the pawn on e2 would be under attack. }
14. f3
{ Or  14.h3  Bxc5  ,  then retreating with the light-squared bishop and targeting the h3 pawn with either ...Qc8 or ...Qd7. Borresen,G  @@StartBracket@@2253@@EndBracket@@-Mikalsen,E @@StartBracket@@2297@@EndBracket@@ Norwegian Team championships 2017. }
14... Bf5 15. fxe4 Bxc5 16. Qxc5 Bxe4
{ Black has a nice outpost on e4 and ideally it would be great to have a knight there versus White's dark-squared bishop, even if it costs a pawn on c6. }
*

