6... e4 7. Ng5 Bxc3
{ Here White might suddenly realize that after the 'normal'  8.Qxc3  Black can play  8...d5  and White can't take the pawn because of  9...Nxd5  and the white knight on g5 hangs! }
8. bxc3 { Or  8.dxc3  Re8 } 8... Re8 9. Qc2 Qe7 10. O-O d6
{ Black nicely controls the center. } *

