7. Nh4
{ Probably this is something that we can discard immediately - in this particular position nobody has played like this so far. It's interesting that with the inclusion of moves ...Nc6 for Black and Nd5 for White this would have been the main move for White. }
7... d6
{ Black is threatening to win the knight on the spot, and the threat can be improved with ...h6 first. }
8. d3 Bxc3 9. bxc3 h6 10. f4
{ A sad choice to save the knight on h4 - now it's important NOT to take the pawn en-passant as that actually but bring two White's pieces into the game immediately! }
10... Na6
{ Black is organizing a game at the queenside and enjoys an excellent position. }
