11. d4
{ White is fighting for the center and postponing the decision to move the knight to e3. }
11... Qh5 12. f3
{ 12.Ne3  would just transpose to  11.Ne3  and  12.d4  which is covered in one of the sidelines of the mainline later. }
12... exf3 13. exf3
{ Tazbir,M @@StartBracket@@2555@@EndBracket@@-Hnydiuk,A @@StartBracket@@2400@@EndBracket@@ Polish championship 2013. }
13... Na5
{ This comes with the idea to still keep tabs, what's happening at the e-file, should White consider Re1. Black is to continue with...Be6 later. White would love to activate his bishop on the a1-h8 diagonal but it's easier said than done. }
14. Ne3 Be6 { Black stops the c-pawn's advancement and goes for the blockade. }
15. Qa4
{ Or  15.Qd3  with the same intentions to push forward the c-pawn, after what Black can respond with  15...Nd5! }
15... b6
{ Black has a nice control of the light squares. Here  16.c4  would meet a cold shower after  16...Nxc4!  and 17... b5 next! }
