12... Bh3 13. Rb1 b6 14. Qa4
{ White might have played  14.a4  instead but after  14...Bxg2  15.Kxg2  Rad8  Black looks very solid with no weaknesses and  16.Rb2  can be calmly answered with  16...Qg6  Abbasov,F @@StartBracket@@2552@@EndBracket@@ -Marzolo,C @@StartBracket@@2487@@EndBracket@@ La Fere op 7th 2008. }
14... Ne7
{ This seems to be the most precise with intentions not only to start an attack at the kingside with ...Nf5 and ...Ng4 later, but also snatch the pawn on e2. Now after  15.Rb5  Black can close the annoying rook with  15...c5  . }
