[White "14. Two Knights: 4.Bg2 and 5.Nf3"]
[Black "Chapter 14 Exercise: #2"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1r1k1/p1p2ppp/1pn2n2/7q/4p3/2P1N1P1/P2PPPBP/1RBQ1RK1 w - - 0 13"]
[SetUp "1"]

13. f3
{ This is a very common motif - White is trying to remove the e4 pawn first before claiming a strong pawn center himself, backed by two bishops. What's the best way for Black to react? }
13... exf3 14. Bxf3 Ng4
{ This maneuver is available for Black also if Rb1 and ...b6 have not been included. White has no time to take the knight on c6. }
15. Nxg4
{ 15.h4  Qe5!  This is not an alternative that White will want to consider. }
15... Bxg4
{ White can't take on c6 due to   16.Bxc6  Rxe2   or  16...Qc5+  , your pick. }
