{ A good prophylactic move - after eventual trades on d5 and opening of the center Black might find that a check on the a2-g8 diagonal could be unpleasant. }
12. Bd2 { This doesn't stop Black to follow the designated plan. } 12... Bd6
13. Nb5
{ Or  13.Nxd5  Bxd5  14.e4  and Black can just retreat with the bishop to g8. With the text move White trades off Black's dark-squared bishop and thus slows down a potential incoming attack, but this also leaves the b3 square quite vulnerable. }
13... a4 14. Rac1 Qd7
{ The d7-square probably is the most flexible square for the black queen, preparing to play next ...Rae8. To do that, Black needs to take care of the a4 pawn next, thus the next couple of moves make perfect sense. }
15. Bf1 Nf6
{ Black takes care of the b3 square and also makes sure not to miss White's e4 thrusts with a tempo - the knight stands well on f6. }
16. e4 Bb3 17. Qb1 Rae8
{ Black should plan an expansion at the kingside or build a brick wall in the center. }
