[White "15. Four Knights: Reversed Sicilian "]
[Black "Chapter 15 Exercise: #2"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2q1r1k/1pp3pp/2nbb3/p2npp2/N7/P2PPN2/1PQ1BPPP/R1BR2K1 w - - 0 13"]
[SetUp "1"]

13. Nc5
{ Black has three options here - trade on c5, defend the bishop on e6, or retreat with the bishop on c8. Which option will you choose, and why? }
13... Bc8
{ Black bishops are precious and you don't want to give them up easily, especially the light-squared bishop. The white knight on c5 won't hold for long.   13...Bxc5  This is also possible but it seriously weakens the dark squares which is something that Black can't take back.  14.Qxc5  a4  At least Black has fixed a weakness on b3. In a slightly different version this option may not be available. }
14. Bd2 Qf6 15. Rac1 b6 { Now it's time to push back the knight. } 16. Na4 Bb7
{ The two bishops could potentially become a powerful force, should the diagonals open. }
