[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "16. Four Knights: with 4.d4"]
[Black "5.Nxd4 and 6.g3: #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d4
{ This move used to popular in the past but nowadays it's considered to be relatively harmless, at least at the GM level. White's idea, similarly to the Scotch opening, is to fight for the center but just like in the Scotch, one of White's pieces moves already for the second time. }
4... exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4
{ Our concept doesn't change - the dark-squared bishop still goes to b4 to attack the knight and if allowed - double the c-pawns. Now White has a little choice. }
6. g3
{ An interesting sideline - White is fianchettoing the light-squared bishop and thus slowing down Black's intention to develop the queenside. There is one major flaw with the plan - Black ruins White's pawn structure and quickly pressures the c4 pawn. }
6... O-O
{ There's no need to rush with the trade on c3 as it's not going anywhere. } 7.
Bg2 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Ne5
{ Suddenly White has got a problem - it needs to do something with the c4 pawn. }
9. Qb3
{ This is seemingly an active move but allows Black to fix the c4 pawn as a weakness. }
9... d6 10. O-O Nfd7
{ A great resource - the kingside knight is heading to the outpost on c5, where it will be also protecting the b7 pawn. }
11. a4 Nc5 12. Qa2 a5
{ Black fixes another weakness on a4 - White can't be happy with the opening's outcome. }
13. Nb3 Nxb3 14. Qxb3 Rb8
{ Black prepares to play ...b6 and ... Bb7 next, trading off the light-squared bishops. Alternatively, there's the idea to play ...Ba6 to target the c4 pawn. }
15. Bf4 Nd7
{ The knight's too important to be traded away - White's dark-squared bishop is a pretty useless piece, even if it's not immediately obvious. }
16. Qb5 b6
{ Black has a solid advantage - he wants to trade off the light-squared bishops but keep the knight alive so that it can target the weaknesses at the queenside. Kryvoruchko,Y @@StartBracket@@2612@@EndBracket@@ -Karjakin,S @@StartBracket@@2732@@EndBracket@@ Ukrainian Team championships 2008. }
