{ Here Black has a choice - you could continue the gambit with  15...Rfe8  with an idea to generate some serious counterplay at the e-file. Should White trade the knights, capture with the queen. Apart from that, Black is threatening to play ...Nc5 }
15... c5 16. Nxe6 { 16.Nb5  a6  doesn't change much. } 16... Qxc3+ 17. Kf2 dxe6
{ The arising position is equal. A correspondence game continued here with  18.Qd3  Qa5  19.Qb3  Rad8  and Black is active enough to secure a draw. Since the white rook on b7 is so active and the white king is weakened, Black is not interested to trade queens, at least not right now. Kamanel del Corral,J @@StartBracket@@2235@@EndBracket@@-Bueno,T @@StartBracket@@2131@@EndBracket@@ CAMO-CERV email 2012. }
