{ It makes sense to start with this move and slow down White's intentions to push forward the e-pawn @@StartBracket@@which doesn't guarantee success@@EndBracket@@. }
17. Nb5 { This jump has been tried in some games. } 17... Qd8 18. e5
{ This is a spectacular idea but tactically it doesn't work. } 18... a6
{ It's important to get rid of the knight first, otherwise after   18...dxe5  White trades the queens and wins the c7 pawn. }
19. Nxc7
{ If you say A, be ready to say B as well, otherwise White has just created a weakness on e5 for no good reason. }
19... Qxc7 20. exd6 Qd8 21. Rxe8+ Qxe8
{ Black is holding and in the following moves played a perfect defense. } 22.
Re1 Qd8 23. Qd5
