Re1+
{ Here Black has a choice - play a sharp game with  15...Kd8  and try to hold the two extra pawns, albeit it's quite obvious that White has the initiative, and then there's the potential Bxd6 sacrifice. There's a safe way out and White will have to force a draw. }
15... Be6 16. Qd5 { Nice idea but Black's defense is also pretty spectacular. }
16... h6 17. h4 { 17.Bc1  meets a very cold shower after  17...O-O! } 17...
Qxg3 { Black has nothing better but neither does White. } 18. Rxe6+ fxe6 19.
Qxe6+ { 19.Qxa5  O-O  and Black wins. } 19... Kd8 20. Bh3
{ White is threatening mate so Black delivers a perpetual check. } 20... Qxc3+
21. Kb1 Qd3+ 22. Ka1 { Last attempt to escape a draw. } 22... Bc3+ 23. Bb2
Bxb2+ 24. Kxb2 Qd2+ 25. Kb3 Qd3+ { The perpetual check is inevitable. } *

