{ Engines seem to like  15.exd6  with a presumably equal position but if there's somebody who's taking risks, it's only White. For example  15...Bxd3  16.Bxd3  cxd6  17.Bxd6  Kd7  ,  followed by ...Bc7. At least I don't see White deliberately going there. }
15... Bb6 16. Re1 O-O-O
{ Black got the better position because of a better pawn structure - the game continued with  17.exd6  cxd6  18.Bg2  Rhe8  19.Bd5  Be3+  20.Kb2  f6  and Black eventually converted the advantage into a win. Poldauf,D @@StartBracket@@2385@@EndBracket@@ -Schlosser,P  @@StartBracket@@2591@@EndBracket@@ Bundesliga 2012. }
