{ This is a typical maneuver - White might win a pawn but Black will be fully developed and the white king is still in the center. }
11. exd6
{ Sooner or later White will have to take the pawn but it might invite Black for a gambit first. }
11... O-O 12. O-O-O
{ Here this is very risky for White as the king will be exposed for an attack. The same position could arise with White castling long first and only then taking on d6. }
12... Be6
