{ Or  18.Rc1  Bxc3+!  19.Rxc3  Qb4+  20.Rb3  and now Black has a decisive attack after  20...Qd2+  21.Ka3  Rc2  . }
18... a6 { Black opens more lines. } 19. a4 axb5 20. axb5 Bd8 21. Rxd8
{ White already doesn't have a choice - that would be a monstrous bishop on f6. }
21... Rxd8 22. Qc3 Rd1
{ White's two extra pawns play no role and Black's attack is already decisive. }
