{ White doesn't have a choice and the pawn seemingly is 'for free' } 25... Rb8
{ The only move - the forced sequence now continues. } 26. Bxc7
{ White could have given a check on e6 first but it doesn't change anything and Black can safely play both ...Kf8 or ...Kh8. }
26... Bf3+ 27. Bxb8 Bxd1+ 28. Ka2 d3
{ A truly odd position - both sides have very strong passed pawns. Here the game could continue with  29.c6  d2  30.Bf4  Bb3+  31.Kxb3  d1=Q+  32.Kxc3  and Black doesn't have anything better than delivering a perpetual check, starting with  32...Qe1+ }
