12... Bb7 13. Bxb5 { A free pawn? } 13... Bxg3 14. hxg3 Ne5
{ Black has a big positional threat ...Ba6 to trade off the light-squared bishops and land the knight on d3 for a devastating effect. Even if White remains alert to the idea. Black controls most of the important squares in the center and the white king will be struggling to find safety. }
