14. h4
{ This weird move comes with an idea to play f4 next and 'force' Black to trade queens. White simply doesn't have any other moves as  14.bxa6  Bxa6  is too much for White to handle, with Black threatening both ...Nd3+ and win the queen in the process, or the more subtle ...c5. }
14... Qg6 { Black provokes the white knight to jump to f4. } 15. Nf4 Qf5
{ Only now the black queen goes to f5 so that nobody can bother it. Now Black is threatening with both ...axb5 and ...Ng4. }
16. b4
{ This is a reasonable attempt to continue the development but now the rook on a1 might be under attack. Now there are some sharp lines but as long as you will remember the first moves, you will be doing great. }
16... Ng4
{ Maybe somebody will find  16...axb5  an easier move to play to meet  17.Bb2  with  17...f6  and a great gambit, but this move is the strongest. }
17. Nd3
{ White defends against the ...Be5 threat but other threats appear, most notably ...Nxf2! }
17... Re4
{ 17...Nxf2  immediately doesn't work as White can include  18.Bb2  intermezzo move with a devastating effect. }
18. Qb2 { The white queen now indirectly defends the f2 square. } 18... Be5
{ The point of this move is to push back the white queen, not to win the rook on a1. }
19. Qa2
{ White is trying to keep the queen on the 2nd rank to protect against the ...Nxf2 threat.  19.Qc2  would have met a massacre, starting with  19...Nxf2!  20.Nxf2  Rxe3+!  21.Kd1  Bf3+  and the game is over. }
19... Rd4
{ This stunning rook sacrifice by force opens more lines and more diagonals. White has no choice. }
20. exd4 Bxd4
{ Black has so many threats - let me present to you a sample line. } 21. Bb2
Re8+ 22. Kd1 Bd5
{ A very important intermezzo check to push away the white queen. } 23. Qb1
Nxf2+
{ The black knight on f2 can't be taken due to a back rank mate, which starts with ...Bb3+ and ends with ...Re1+. }
24. Kc2 Bxb2 { It's time to collect the spoils of war. } 25. Kxb2 Nxh1
{ Now after several moves the storm is over and we can evaluate the position. }
26. bxa6 Qf6+ 27. Kc2 Qxa6
{ There's material equality on the board but because of the weakened king White is doomed. }
