12. Qxd5 Rb8 { Black for the pawn has the initiative. } 13. Qd1 Bb7 14. Kf1
{ This is already necessary, otherwise after  14.Nf3  Black will just take with the knight and if White wants to keep the pawn on b5, they will have to take with the g-pawn and have an exposed king. }
14... Qg5
{ Now after  15.Nf3  Nxf3  16.gxf3  Qf5  the initiative belongs to Black, threatening both ...Qh3+ and ...Be5, slowing down White's development at the queenside. }
