[SetUp "1"]

9. Be2 { What's the best plan for Black here? } 9... b6
{ The correct answer - pressure the weak c4 pawn and close the center. } 10.
O-O Ba6 11. Re1 e4
{ The reason why the center should be closed is not to miss any active counter-attacks in the center. Don't forget - your opponent might sacrifice the weak pawn and seek his chances elsewhere. The best bet would be the center. }
12. Nd2 Na5
{ White is on the defensive and lacks an active plan. Black shouldn't miss White's Ba3-b4 resource and this is when ...c5 will make most sense. }
