[SetUp "1"]

10. g3
{ White just stopped Black's idea from playing ...Nf4 but is ready to sacrifice the pawn on d4. What should you do? }
10... exd4
{ Some general advice - don't be afraid to accept sacrifices. Very often it's the most principled approach but also the best. Specifically here Black has enough resources to hold everything. }
11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. cxd4 Qxd4
{ The knight on h5 is hanging but so is the white rook on a1. } 13. Bb2 Qc5 14.
e5 { White is threatening with Bxh5 again - Black doesn't have a choice here. }
14... g6 15. exd6
{ The critical moment - White wants to play Qc3 next and enjoy great compensation. What's the most precise move here? }
15... Qb4+ { Black wins a critical tempo, taking away the c3 square. } 16. Bc3
Qxd6
{ Black is solid enough - White has a compensation for the pawn but not more. }
