12... Qxe5 13. Bb2 d4
{ I think that the mood here for White should be pretty low @@StartBracket@@Black is crushing me right after the opening@@EndBracket@@. I'll illustrate to you a couple of mistakes that White could make right here. }
14. Bc4
{ It should be pretty clear for White that staying for so long at the center had been hazardous for the health. For example,  14.f3  Nxc5  14.Qd2  Qe7! }
14... Rhe8
{ 14...Qe7  here no longer is good as Black will be missing the ...Bg6 move at the end of the line, which I explained in one of the previous sidelines. }
15. Bxd4 { This is one more mistake that White can make. } 15... Qf5 16. f3
{ Or  16.O-O  Bf3!  with a threat to continue with ...Qg6+, ...Ng3+ and win the white queen on c2. }
16... Rxd4
{ Luckily Black has no choice but to play beautiful chess as  16...Bxf3  17.O-O  is just lost. }
17. exd4 Nd6+
{ Black has a decisive attack. The engine likes  17...Nf2+  a little more, but the lines are more computer-like. }
18. Kd2
{ Here  18.Kd1  allows  18...Bxf3+  and Black collects back everything with interest. }
18... Qf4+ 19. Kc3 Re3+ 20. Kb4 Qxd4
{ The naked white king against two heavy pieces, a knight and some pawns doesn't stand a chance. }
21. fxg4 b6 { This should end with a quick mate. } *

