14... Rhe8
{ 14...Qe7  here no longer is good as Black will be missing the ...Bg6 move at the end of the line, which I explained in one of the previous sidelines. }
15. O-O { Further from the sin! Only a skilled player would make it this far. }
15... Bf3
{ Alright, time to finish the game - White found all of the best moves so a perpetual check is good.   15...Qg5  16.f4  Qxc5  and the following exchange sacrifice on d4 keeps the game alive with chances for both sides. }
16. gxf3
{ White has no choice -   16.Be2  allows Black to shine once more with  16...Bxg2!!  17.Kxg2  Qf5!  and there's no defense from either ...Qg6+ with ...Ng3+ or including ...d3 with the same idea. }
16... Qg5+ 17. Kh1 Qh5 18. fxe4
{ 18.Rg1  loses to  18...d3!  19.Bxd3  Qxf3+  20.Rg2  Rxd3  and there's the fork on f2, and the same remedy is after  18.Be2  ,  only with a slightly different execution. }
18... Qf3+ 19. Kg1 Qg4+ { Draw by a perpetual check. } *

