13. O-O Bb7
{ This bishop will be bothering White for a long time. Black wants to play next ...a5, ...d6, ...Rae8 and organize activities at the kingside. }
14. Bd2 a5
{ The most consistent with the plan - now White already was threatening with b4. }
15. f3 f5
{ I want to mention here is that you don't have to be afraid of White playing e4 - then you can always fire up the center with the f5 move. However, it feels good to pressure the e3 pawn as a potential weakness. }
16. Rae1 Rae8 17. Bd1
{ White finally has managed to reroute the light-squared bishop to c2 but there's no attack. Black can be pretty active himself at the kingside. }
17... Rf6 18. Bc2 Rd6
{ Remember that I advised you not to rush with the ...d6 move? Here's the hidden bonus. }
19. Qc3 Qg5 20. Re2 Qh5
{ Black is looking towards to bother White at the kingside a little while White is preparing a3 and b4 to get rid of the knight. It will look great on e6 anyway. }
