12... Rxd5 13. Bc4
{ It's a tempting move to push back the black rook as the pawn on f7 hangs. }
13... Rd7 14. Bb2 { 14.h3  Nxe5! } 14... Re8
{ Black targets the pawn on e5 and keeps many threats alive, like ...Nc5, or ...Bxf3 and ...Nxf2 next with ...Rd2+ to follow. }
15. h3
{ The same applies for  15.Rc1  White might try to play   15.Be2  but after  15...Nc5  16.Rd1  Rxd1+  and ...Be6 next, Black snatches back the pawn on a2. }
15... Bxf3 16. gxf3 Nxf2
{ A nice idea to know - the knight is traded for one of White's bishops. } 17.
Kxf2
{ Or  17.Rg1  Nd3+  18.Bxd3  Rxd3  19.Ke2  and here Black has  19...Red8  to save the pawn on g7 just in time as ... Rd2+ is a threat White can't ignore. }
17... Rd2+ 18. Kg3 Rxb2 19. f4 f6
{ At the moment White has to solve a problem, what to do with the e5 pawn. } *

