9. dxe5 { The main and the most principled move at White's disposal. } 9... Ne4
{ Now White has two major choices here - either retreat with the queen to c2 or a3 as everything else seems to be worse. }
10. Qb3
{ Or  10.Qd3  Nc5  and it should lead to the same position as the pawn on d5 is untouchable due to  11...Rd8  and the white queen is trapped. This is a very risky approach for White who will be walking a tightrope. }
