10... Re8 { Suddenly the white knight is in trouble. } 11. Ng5
{ White might try to escape with  11.d4  but then after  11...Nxd4  12.e3  Nf5  Black has regained the pawn and is better. }
11... Qxg5 { Now White has a little choice here. } 12. Bxc6
{ Aronian played this but it looks quite dangerous for White. } 12... bxc6 13.
d4 Qh5 14. dxc5 e4
{ Black holds the initiative and the extra pawn is meaningless. } 15. h4
{ Aronian,L @@StartBracket@@2799@@EndBracket@@ -Caruana,F @@StartBracket@@2807@@EndBracket@@ Saint Louis Rapid 2017, in the game Black didn't play the best continuation. }
15... Bg4 16. Re1 f6
{ White will need to lead a very tough defense in order not to get mated. For example,  17.Be3  g5  18.hxg5  Kf7  and after ...Rh8 it's only a matter of time for decisive threats. }
