12... Nd4
{ Given the circumstances, now this plan looks best - Black wants to continue with ...c6 }
13. Nxd4
{ If White starts with  13.Re1  with some future ideas to trade the black dark-squared bishop on b6 and recapture on f3 with a pawn to pressure the black pawn on e5, then it's best simply to include  13...Nxf3  and skip this idea altogether, as White has to take with the bishop. }
13... exd4 14. Re1 c6
{ Again, with an easy game for Black - the white pawn on e2 is quite weak. If White will play e4, Black almost always takes ...dxe3 en passant. }
