{ White going for Black's dark-squared bishop suddenly meets a spectacular finale. }
14... Bb7 15. Qa4
{ If  15.Qb5  then  15...Bf3!!  feels like a cold shower with ...Bxf2+ threat incoming. }
15... Qd5 16. e4 Qxd3
{ Probably White already has nothing better to do than taking on b6 and try to salvage the game. Being stubborn is not always good. }
17. Nxe5 Qe2 18. Qc4 Qh5
{ The attack is too strong - Black ignores the fork on d7 and now it's time for White to test, why. }
19. Nd7 Rfe8 20. Nxb8 { Or  20.Nxb6  Bxe4! } 20... Rxe4 21. Qc3 Rh4
{ A spectacular finish - White is getting slaughtered. } *

