11. Nc4
{ White can immediately target the e5 pawn by threatening with Bxc6 and Nxe5 next. }
11... Be6
{ Among all choices I like this one the most - Black is threatening to play ...Bd5 to trade off the light-squared bishops. }
12. Bxc6
{ What else? This seems to be quite principled - White doubles Black's pawns and gets some targets to pressure while Black will have his counter chances at the kingside. After  12.Be3  Black can just trade the bishops with  12...Bxe3  13.Nxe3  and  13...Nd4  looks good enough as Bxb7 is not a threat due to ...Rb8-b2. }
12... bxc6 13. Nxe5
{ This is just not good - Black wins some material thanks to a simple trick. }
13... Bh3
{ White will have to continue the game with a questionable compensation. Now  14.Re1  loses to  14...Qd4  and   14.Nxc6  to  14...Qd5  and the mate threat on g2. }
