[Result "*"]

1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. e3 Bb4 5. Nd5 e4 6. Ng1 O-O 7. a3 Bd6 8. Qc2
{ The reason why this continuation is considered to be dangerous for White, you can find in Chapter 18. }
8... Re8 9. Ne2 b5 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6 11. cxb5 Ne5 12. Qxe4 Bb7 13. Qd4 a6 14. f4
{ Recently White has been testing   14.h4  ,  just to prepare f4. If this is the best approach for White, there's something wrong with the entire line. }
14... Qh4+ 15. Ng3 Ng4 16. bxa6 Bc6
{ This is very strong - White's queenside pawns are irrelevant and the light-squared bishop is a critical piece for the initiative. The threat of ...Nxh2 remains. }
17. Ke2
{ White is back at the Bongcloud ways but it's not clear what else to suggest. Black shouldn't miss the Qxg7+ and Nf5+. }
17... g6
{ 17...Be7  Technically this was a little more precise, and only then ...g6, but it shouldn't change the outcome of the game. }
18. b4 Be7 { Rearranging the bishop to f6. } 19. Rb1
{ We're witnessing a show of a total domination - White is up three pawns and yet he's totally powerless! White's out of ideas.   19.Ne4!  White should had tried to complicate the game and sell something back...even if it's a rook!  19...Bxe4  20.Qxe4  Bf6  Seemingly game over? Wait - White's still got those three pawns.  21.g3  Qh5  22.Qf3  This initiates a forced sequence - White trades off the queens.  22...Bxa1  23.h3  Nf6  24.Qxh5  Nxh5  25.Kf3  Nf6  Technically this is a winning position as Black is up a rook but those passed pawns, combined with two strong bishops, make a strange impression. Either way, this was White's best chance. }
19... Bf6 20. Qc5 Nxh2
{ Winning back one pawn, the knight on g3 is hanging - Black wrapped up game very quickly. }
21. b5 Qg4+ 22. Kd3
{ Nothing can save White here, not even a miracle.   22.Kf2  This would be great, if not for that only Black's move.  22...Bh4!  23.bxc6  Bxg3+  24.Kg1  Qh4  Black has a decisive attack and what's happening at the queenside, can't affect the outcome.  25.e4  25...Qxf4  26.Bb2  Ng4  White collapses as he can't deal with both threats. }
22... Nxf1
{ There's a simple rule - don't go for the mate but just collect material. You can mate White later. }
23. Rxf1 Bxg2 { White is losing a lot of material. } 24. Qxc7 Bxf1+
{ Black is up a rook and now after   25.Nxf1  Qf5+  Black wins another. } *

